  URL: https://magnus919.com/notes/oh-my-zsh-alternatives/
  Antidote is a Zsh plugin manager made from the ground up thinking about performance. It is fast because it can do things concurrently, and generates an ultra- ...

  --- Content ---
  # [oh-my-zsh alternatives](https://magnus919.com/notes/oh-my-zsh-alternatives/)
  
  2025-01-192 min read (276 words)
  
  # [oh-my-zsh](https://magnus919.com/tags/oh-my-zsh/)
  # [zsh](https://magnus919.com/tags/zsh/)
  # [macOS](https://magnus919.com/tags/macos/)
  # [linux](https://magnus919.com/tags/linux/)![oh-my-zsh alternatives](https://magnus919.com/null)
  
  ## Table of Contents
  
  # Background [\#](https://magnus919.com/notes/oh-my-zsh-alternatives/\#background)
  
  I’ve been a `zsh` user for a long time, both on Linux (where it’s not the default) and ~~OS X~~ macOS (where it now _is_ the default).
  
  The first thing I used to do on new machines is port all of my `.oh-my-zsh` stuff over.
  
  [Oh My Zsh](https://ohmyz.sh/) is not bad! This is not mean to slam the project at all.
  
  But I’ve recently (Jan 2025) upgraded to a new [Mac](https://magnus919.com/tags/mac/) Mini M4 and I thought maybe I should see what else is out there. If there’s something that’s _good enough_ without being quite as large in size.
  
  # Alternatives [\#](https://magnus919.com/notes/oh-my-zsh-alternatives/\#alternatives)
  
  ## Antidote [\#](https://magnus919.com/notes/oh-my-zsh-alternatives/\#antidote)
  
  [Antidote](https://antidote.sh/) is the only one I’m really messing with right now (Jan 2025).
  
  > Antidote is a Zsh plugin manager made from the ground up thinking about performance.
  >
  > It is fast because it can do things concurrently, and generates an ultra-fast static plugin file that you can easily load from your Zsh config.
  
  The author of Antidote also [claims](https://www.reddit.com/r/zsh/comments/13ekut5/comment/jjqhxzb/):
  
  > You can use antidote to load [oh-my-zsh plugins](https://github.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/wiki/Plugins) pretty easily.
  
  I’m going to give it a try.
  
  ### ~/.zshrc [\#](https://magnus919.com/notes/oh-my-zsh-alternatives/\#zshrc)
  
  zshCopy
  
  ```zsh
  autoload -Uz compinit
  compinit
  
  . "$HOME/.cargo/env"
  
  zstyle :omz:plugins:iterm2 shell-integration yes
  
  # Set OMZ variables if you want.
  ZSH_THEME="kphoen"
  
  # Set any helper functions used by your antidote config.
  function is-macos() {
  	[[ $OSTYPE == darwin* ]]
  }
  
  # source antidote
  source ~/.antidote/antidote.zsh
  
  # initialize plugins statically with ${ZDOTDIR:-~}/.zsh_plugins.txt
  antidote load
  ```
  
  ### ~/.zsh\_plugins.txt [\#](https://magnus919.com/notes/oh-my-zsh-alternatives/\#zsh_pluginstxt)
  
  zshCopy
  
  ```zsh
  #.zsh_plugins.txt
  
  # use-omz needs to be FIRST
  getantidote/use-omz
  
  # Add in some oh-my-zsh stuff
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:lib
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/colored-man-pages
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/docker-compose
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/gh
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/git
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/git-prompt
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/rsync
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/ssh
  
  # Add macOS specific plugins
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/brew conditional:is-macos
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/macos conditional:is-macos
  ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh path:plugins/iterm2 conditional:is-macos
  # zsh-users
  zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions
  zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting
  ```
